Male terminalia. Tergite VIII (
Figs 43–44
) sparsely covered with short setae at margin of the apical half, with 5 longer setae at apex; disc short, nearly as long as wide, sides gradually constricted towards apex, apex broadly rounded. Sternite VIII (
Figs 43–44
) sparsely covered with short setae at sides of middle of apex, spiculum relictum short. Spiculum gastrale (
Figs 45–47
) Y-shaped, slender, distinctly longer than sternite VIII. Tegmen (
Figs 48–52
) nearly flat, about as long as penis; apical 2 / 3 of the dorsal surface of parameres sparsely covered with short setae, denser and longer setae apically, ventral surface of parameres sparsely covered with short setae, denser setae at apex and at insides of base, longer setae apically, parameres separated from each other, but nearly connected in the middle, rounded apically; phallobase more than 2.0 times as long as parameres. Aedeagus (
Figs 53–55
) curved and thin in profile; dorsal struts short, nearly 1 / 3 as long as penis, weakly curved in profile; dorsal plate rounded apically; ventral plate distinctly longer than dorsal plate, bearing a small round projection at apex.
